    <h1>3 POEMAS DE VIDA [NI CURSIS, NI ROMÁNTICOS]</h1>
    <P> Todos algunas vez nos hemo sentido atraídos por la poesía; sin embargo, esta a veces peca de cursis y romántica, dos atributo que a los poco románticos y seguros de sí mismos, nos desalienta. Es por eso que hoy te he traído 5 poemas reales, escrito y dirigidos por escritos de verdad. Y no escritores que juegan al romanticismo.
    <h4>Tabla de contenidos</h4>
<ul>
    <li><a href="#fear">Fear</a></li>
    <li><a href="#tipasa">Return to Tipasa</a></li>
    <li><a href="#kafka">Kafka in the short</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="fear">Fear</h2>
<p>The river needs to take the risk <br>
of entering the ocean <br>
because only then will fear disappear,<br>
because that’s where the river will know <br>
it’s not about disappearing into the ocean,<br>
but of becoming the ocean.</p>

<h2 id="tipasa">Return to Tipasa</h2>
<p>And that makes me happy. <br>
For it says that no matter <br>
how hard the world pushes against me, <br> 
within me, there’s <br>
something stronger – something better, <br>
pushing right back.</p>

<h2 id="kafka">Kafka in the short</h2>
<p> And once the storm is over,<br>
you won’t remember how you made it through,<br> 
how you managed to survive. <br>
You won’t even be sure, <br>
whether the storm is really over. <br>
But one thing is certain. <br>
When you come out of the storm, <br> 
you won’t be the same person who walked in. <br>
That’s what this storm’s all about.</p>


